    {
      "id": "1518176083642552360",
      "type": "Reply",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-21T08:49:44.688+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": "2026-06-21T08:51:16.595+00:00",
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Cheaper by which metric? Because a Sky130 TinyTapeout shuttle contains roughly 3x as many tiles as a GF180MCU one (512 vs 160), while the Chipfoundry slot is only twice as expensive (15k vs 7.5k). Of course that ignores the fact that with wafer.space you get many more parts back, but if we ignore that, Sky130 seems cheaper than GF180MCU relative to the amount of logic you get, not the other way around.",
      "author": {
        "id": "210716756778418187",
        "name": "olexorus",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Oliver",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2026-06_media/0-EB806.png"
