      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Ah, makes sense. But I thought the number of parts doesn't actually make a big difference for price (at these low parts counts, e.g. 10 vs 1000), it's just an arbitrary decision by the people running the MPW shuttle to make people use more expensive services for production use. So while that is a big advantage of wafer.space, it shouldn't say much about the production cost of Sky130? I.e. they could decide to ship more parts and it wouldn't change the price significantly?",
