      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "There's the Japanese one, but it's a 1000nm 5V CMOS node.\nAnd I don't think it offers ldmos, and at best it mildly beats w.s. per-transistor \"if you ignore not getting 1~2 orders of magnitude fewer dies\".\n(I believe figuring out how to package smaller dies on w.s. would fully cancel that per-custom-design cost difference by making 1/8th tiles \"usable\".)",
